<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - FULLER 10 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS - DISASSEMBLE - AUXILIARY
        COUNTERSHAFT
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="disassemble" graphiccount="2">
        <title>AUXILIARY COUNTERSHAFT</title>
        <para>See
            <hotlnk xrefid="f1303285">Figure 85.</hotlnk>
        </para>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>Do not use a puller against the flat washer on the rear of the countershaft when removing the
                    bearing. The washer will break.
                </para>
            </caution>
            <caution>
                <para>Bearing removal will likely damage the bearings. If the bearings are damaged in any way upon
                    removal, do not re-use them.
                </para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
        <para>Use a bearing puller to remove the bearings (
            <hotlnk xrefid="f1303286">Figure 86)</hotlnk>. It may be necessary to cut and remove the steel cage and
            rollers from the bearings to allow a bearing puller to fit correctly.
        </para>
        <figure id="f1303285" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg13/G1303285.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" resolution="72"/>
            <caption>Figure 85. Auxiliary Countershaft Assembly</caption>
        </figure>
        <figure id="f1303286" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg13/G1303286.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="232px" resolution="72"/>
            <caption>Figure 86. Removal Of Bearings</caption>
        </figure>
    </svcproc>
